LAPIOTA INSTALL
    (version 0.0.1)

_______________________________________________________________________________
1   Install

1.1     Mount lam.root -> ROOTDIR

1.2     (optional) Pre-init env vars:
1.2.1       Set HOME to your home directory, default is ROOTDIR/home/USERNAME
1.2.2       Set CYGWIN_ROOT to your installed cygwin path, if exists.

1.3     Run ROOTDIR/bin/lapiota-install

1.4     Refresh env vars:
1.4.1       Right click on My Computer, open Properties page
1.4.2       Select Advanced tab page, click Environment Variables

1.5     Right click on ROOTDIR/.cat, run Add Lapiota Module

1.6    Run Start Menu/Programs/Startup/lapiota-boot

_______________________________________________________________________________
2   User Configs

2.1     HOME/etc/hotkeys
        defines user hot keys in autohotkey syntax.

2.2     HOME/etc/startup.d
        all shell scripts in this directory is runned when lapiota boots.

2.3     HOME/etc/lams
        each line in the format of:
            MOUNTPOINT DEVICE
        the fstype is auto determined, currently only .pgd is supported.

2.4     HOME/etc/crontab
        contains user cron tasks.

_______________________________________________________________________________
3   Predefined hot keys

3.1     System Control

        CTRL-ALT-DEL    force reboot
                        this overrides the default action: Open Task Manager,
                        which can also invoked by CTRL-SHIFT-ESC.
        CTRL-WIN-ESC    go to sleep (for keyboards without SLEEP key)

3.2     Hotkey Daemon

        ALT-WIN-E       edit system hotkeys
        ALT-WIN-R       reload hotkeys
        ALT-WIN-S       enable/disable hotkeys

3.3     Multimedia

        APPS-<NUM +>    volumn up
        APPS-<NUM ->    volumn down
        APPS-<NUM />    mute

3.4     Windows

        WIN-PGUP        scroll up
        WIN-PGDN        scroll down

        WIN-DOWN        hide the current window
        WIN-LEFT        show hidden windows list
        WIN-UP          restore last hidden window
        WIN-RIGHT       restore all hidden windows

3.5     Utilities

        WIN-A           ANSI console
        WIN-B           Big console
        WIN-C           Console
        WIN-M           Metapad
        WIN-N           Notepad++
        WIN-P           Paint.net (may be replaced by GIMP in future)
        WIN-Q           Quick Logger
        WIN-T           Cygwin Terminal or Xwin Terminal (if Xwin has been started)
        WIN-X           start Xwin
        WIN-=           bc desktop calculator
        WIN-F2          stardict

3.6     Programming

        WIN-SHIFT-E     Emacs
        WIN-SHIFT-J     Eclipse
        CTRL-ALT-ENTER  Evaluate expression in eclipse

_______________________________________________________________________________
